+{"id":"frankentorch-r38w","title":"Fix ft-nn MultiLabelMarginLoss autograd via pair-wise broadcast [child of cq0b]","description":"MultiLabelMarginLoss in ft-nn computes pair-wise margin between target and non-target classes per sample. Composable through outer-style broadcast (unsqueeze + sub) to build the (i, j) pair difference tensor, then mask by (target_mask outer non_target_mask), apply relu, sum, divide by C.","notes":"Fixed in this commit. Composed ft-nn MultiLabelMarginLoss through pair-wise broadcast (unsqueeze + expand + sub) → relu → masked-sum:
   x_i = unsqueeze(input, 2) → [batch, c, 1] expanded
   x_j = unsqueeze(input, 1) → [batch, 1, c] expanded
   pair_diff = x_i - x_j     → [batch, c, c]
   relu_margin = relu(1 - pair_diff)
   pair_mask = (target_mask_i outer non_target_mask_j)
   per_sample = sum_dim(sum_dim(relu_margin * pair_mask, 2), 1) / c
   reduce per Reduction.

The target masks are non-grad target-derived leaves; the rest of the chain is autograd-aware so gradients flow to input. ft-nn lib tests: 517.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-30T23:22:28.325612378Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-30T23:23:55.471953004Z","closed_at":"2026-04-30T23:23:55.469583257Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
